rrow icon n n n n n n Down arrow icon FAQs When is Commencement  Spring Commencement Ceremonies will be held in May during or immediately following finals week  The schedule of days  times  and locations of the ceremonies will be available closer to the date of the commencement  Check our Schedule Page for updates When do I Participate in commencement  Once you have verified with your college that all degree requirements are met  or will have been met  by the end of the semester you can participate in commencement  If you complete your degree requirements during the spring semester you must participate in the spring commencement ceremony  If you complete your degree requirements during the summer or fall semesters  you must participate in the fall commencement ceremony  All students are expected to attend the commencement ceremony for the semester in which they have completed all degree requirements How do I know if I am eligible to graduate  Undergraduate students should check with the academic advisor assigned by the college  Graduate students must check with his or her home department  For any additional information regarding degree requirements please visit  Degree Requirements How long will the commencement ceremony last  Approximately two hours How do I purchase my regalia  Click here Click here How many tickets do I receive for my commencement ceremony  Only the December commencement  Spring LAS commencement  and the Spring Pharmacy commencement issue tickets  After applying to graduate and registering for commencement  students should receive an e mail regarding ticket information  For any additional information on tickets to commencement ceremonies  please contact the college issuing the degree or e mail to commencement uic edu What time should I arrive for my commencement  It is recommended that students arrive one hour before the commencement ceremony is set to begin  This way they can check in and find the appropriate seat before the beginning of the ceremony  Doors at the UIC Pavilion open for guests approximately one hour before the ceremony and remain open until the end of the ceremony Will my name be called during the commencement ceremony  Yes  all students attending the ceremony will be individually recognized after the conferral of the degrees I have been awarded university honors  how will I be recognized during my commencement ceremony  Latin honors listed below will appear on UIC transcripts for undergraduate students participating commencement ceremonies honoring student who earned their degrees at UIC  Summa cum laude will be distinguished with gold cords  Magna cum laude will be distinguished with silver cords  and cum laude will be distinguished with bronze cords Summa cum laude       to      to   For more information on the Latin Honors policy please refer to the Registrar website I have been awarded college honors  will I be recognized during commencement  Each college or department may choose different ways to honor its outstanding graduates  If you have received a college or department honor or distinction  please direct all questions to your advisor  department  or college Is seating available for disabled hearing impaired guests  faculty members  and students  Yes  to make accommodation requests please contact UIC Venues and Events at                 When is my college commencement reception  As commencement approaches  our Schedule Page will include the days  times  and locations of commencement receptions  Any information not available on the schedule page will be distributed by the college issuing the degree Where can I purchase graduation announcements  Graduation announcements can be purchased through the Jostens website I am a faculty member  who do I contact to order a cap and gown  Regalia orders for faculty are ordered online through our website  Please order before the deadline to ensure the proper regalia can be provided  Click here to place the order Where can I get information regarding hotel accommodations near UIC  For information on how to get to campus  to view a campus map When will I receive my diploma  Diplomas will be mailed to graduates beginning   to   weeks after your degree has been awarded  All degrees will be posted onto student records   to   weeks after grades have been processed  Name and or address changes must be made by the last day of the term  Please refer to the Registrar website for more information Where can I get additional information about UIC Spring commencements  For additional information send an e mail to commencement uic edu What are the university degree requirements  Degree requirements are specific to the college awarding the degree as well as the level and field of study  To view more information on degree requirements please visit  http   catalog uic edu ucat   http   catalog uic edu ucat   n nUIC Logo n n n n UIC Logo  n          Commencement n         Contact                commencement uic edu Social Media Accounts UIC edu links UIC edu Academic Calendar Athletics Campus Directory Disability Resources Emergency Information Event Calendar Job Openings Library Maps UIC Today UI Health Veterans Affairs Privacy Statement Campuses University of Illinois System Urbana Champaign Springfield Cookie Settings 